        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[YouTube Remonetizes Dr Disrespect, The Creator Of Final Fantasy Is Making One Last RPG, And More Top Stories]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-the-sims-pokemon-tcg-pocket-gaming-news-1851752785</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/youtube-remonetizes-dr-disrespect-the-creator-of-final-fantasy-is-making-one-last-rpg-and-more-top-stories.1097781/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-the-sims-pokemon-tcg-pocket-gaming-news-1851752785<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="947d4e7ea432c858045a8713e04c02d2" data-recommend-id="image://947d4e7ea432c858045a8713e04c02d2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA / Mobygames<!-- -->, <!-- -->Koei Tecmo<!-- -->, <!-- -->Lighthousegamess / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Creatures, Inc. / DeNA / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Square Enix / Moby Games<!-- -->, <!-- -->BioWare / EA<!-- -->, <!-- -->The Pokémon Company<!-- -->, <!-- -->Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->don_cv / eBay<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->DrDisrespect / YouTube / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Hello Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="947d4e7ea432c858045a8713e04c02d2" data-recommend-id="image://947d4e7ea432c858045a8713e04c02d2" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>This week saw the return of the first 2 <em>Sims </em>games, the revelation that another big open-world samurai game is coming to PC alongside <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows</em>, and YouTube allowing controversial streamer Guy “Dr Disrespect” Beahm remonetize his channel. Also, <em>No Man’s Sky </em>got a colossal update, and card trading came to <em>Pokémon TCG Pocket</em>, leading the game’s creators to try to prevent real-money trading from flourishing. These stories and more await in the pages ahead.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="b5658fb35ddf996378f01f0919923cc8" data-recommend-id="image://b5658fb35ddf996378f01f0919923cc8" data-format="png" data-width="1065" data-height="600" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Sims characters prepare for the re-launch. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Sims characters prepare for the re-launch. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->EA / Mobygames</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b5658fb35ddf996378f01f0919923cc8" data-recommend-id="image://b5658fb35ddf996378f01f0919923cc8" data-format="png" data-width="1065" data-height="600" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Sims characters prepare for the re-launch. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Fans of <em>The Sims</em>&nbsp;<span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://simscommunity.info/2025/01/27/sims-1-sims-2-rerelease-teaser/&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://simscommunity.info/2025/01/27/sims-1-sims-2-rerelease-teaser/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">have their hopes up</a></span> that the original two games will finally be remastered for modern platforms after Electronic Arts cryptically teased them in a new 25th anniversary promo video. <em>Kotaku</em> understands that <em>The Sims 1</em> and <em>The Sims 2</em> will both be re-released on PC before the end of the month.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/sims-1-2-remaster-pc-buy-ea-maxis-steam-1851748658&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/sims-1-2-remaster-pc-buy-ea-maxis-steam-1851748658">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="ba96a6585899f068eeadfff1f52ddd65" data-recommend-id="image://ba96a6585899f068eeadfff1f52ddd65" data-format="png" data-width="1869" data-height="1050" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Shadowy figures fight in a street. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Shadowy figures fight in a street. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Koei Tecmo</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ba96a6585899f068eeadfff1f52ddd65" data-recommend-id="image://ba96a6585899f068eeadfff1f52ddd65" data-format="png" data-width="1869" data-height="1050" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Shadowy figures fight in a street. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>  <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows</em> just can’t catch a break. Ubisoft’s big open-world samurai RPG isn’t the only one coming out in 2025, or even in March. In addition to <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ghost-of-yotei-tsushima-protagonist-atsu-wolf-ps5-1851657667?_gl=1*3x1zt2*_ga*ODE3ODM5ODIyLjE3MjA0NjY0NTg.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNzk4Njk5NC4yOS4xLjE3Mzc5ODg2ODUuMzIuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ghost-of-yotei-tsushima-protagonist-atsu-wolf-ps5-1851657667?_gl=1*3x1zt2*_ga*ODE3ODM5ODIyLjE3MjA0NjY0NTg.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNzk4Njk5NC4yOS4xLjE3Mzc5ODg2ODUuMzIuMC4w"><em>Ghost of Tsushima</em>’s sequel</a></span> arriving later this year, <em>Rise of the Ronin</em> just got a date for its PC port and it’s only a week <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ubisoft-assassins-creed-shadows-delay-march-february-1851736266&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ubisoft-assassins-creed-shadows-delay-march-february-1851736266">before <em>Assassin’s Creed Shadows </em>comes out</a></span>.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/rise-ronin-pc-port-steam-release-date-open-world-rpg-1851748237&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/rise-ronin-pc-port-steam-release-date-open-world-rpg-1851748237">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4e6a4f2e55b531d0a54077beddd1e443" data-recommend-id="image://4e6a4f2e55b531d0a54077beddd1e443" data-format="jpg" data-width="1376" data-height="774" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The prototype Nintendo GameCube, purple, seen from above." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The prototype Nintendo GameCube, purple, seen from above." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->don_cv / eBay</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4e6a4f2e55b531d0a54077beddd1e443" data-recommend-id="image://4e6a4f2e55b531d0a54077beddd1e443" data-format="jpg" data-width="1376" data-height="774" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The prototype Nintendo GameCube, purple, seen from above." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Only recently, I passed on my GameCube to my nephew who was just starting college. He wanted something to play <em>Mario Kart</em> and <em>GoldenEye</em> on with new friends, and apparently it’s proving a hit. But this means I don’t have a GameCube. So let’s check eBay... - John Walker <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-gamecube-space-world-2000-ebay-prototype-1851751411&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-gamecube-space-world-2000-ebay-prototype-1851751411">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="6d51ad8670ef3fc434503e1094ab0683" data-recommend-id="image://6d51ad8670ef3fc434503e1094ab0683" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows the AI art for the cover of Mariostro Strikers. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image shows the AI art for the cover of Mariostro Strikers. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Lighthousegamess / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6d51ad8670ef3fc434503e1094ab0683" data-recommend-id="image://6d51ad8670ef3fc434503e1094ab0683" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows the AI art for the cover of Mariostro Strikers. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Over on the Xbox Store you can currently find <em>Mariostro Strikers: Soccer League, </em>a newly released game that is clearly a knock-off of the popular Nintendo-published <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mario-strikers-battle-league-review-nintendo-switch-mul-1849047762&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mario-strikers-battle-league-review-nintendo-switch-mul-1849047762"><em>Mario Strikers</em></a></span> series. And yes, the cover is an awful AI-generated nightmare.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/new-mario-strikers-xbox-clone-knock-off-ai-art-nintendo-1851751729&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/new-mario-strikers-xbox-clone-knock-off-ai-art-nintendo-1851751729">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="e0cef375241f03af5e549687351869d6" data-recommend-id="image://e0cef375241f03af5e549687351869d6" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Pikachu Ex and other cards appear in front of forest art. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Pikachu Ex and other cards appear in front of forest art. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Creatures, Inc. / DeNA / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e0cef375241f03af5e549687351869d6" data-recommend-id="image://e0cef375241f03af5e549687351869d6" data-format="png" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Pikachu Ex and other cards appear in front of forest art. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The creators of <em>Pokémon TCG Pocket </em>have issued a warning to all players not to tamper with game data or participate in real <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-trading-rules-gold-cards-date-1851741957&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-trading-rules-gold-cards-date-1851741957">money trades</a></span>, or risk getting their accounts banned. The crackdown comes right before card trading and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-new-set-lucario-sinnoh-dialga-palkia-1851746013&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-new-set-lucario-sinnoh-dialga-palkia-1851746013">a new Space-Time Smackdown set</a></span> are added to the mobile hit.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-real-money-trades-space-time-set-1851748471&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-real-money-trades-space-time-set-1851748471">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3f63369fe54184ed21e2afab532d2e9f" data-recommend-id="image://3f63369fe54184ed21e2afab532d2e9f" data-format="png" data-width="1656" data-height="934" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Guy &quot;DrDisrespect&quot; Beahm appears in a recent YouTube video. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Guy &quot;DrDisrespect&quot; Beahm appears in a recent YouTube video. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->DrDisrespect / YouTube / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3f63369fe54184ed21e2afab532d2e9f" data-recommend-id="image://3f63369fe54184ed21e2afab532d2e9f" data-format="png" data-width="1656" data-height="934" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Guy &quot;DrDisrespect&quot; Beahm appears in a recent YouTube video. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Guy “Dr Disrespect” Beahm can start making money from YouTube again after the Google-owned video platform remonetized his channel of over 4.5 million subscribers on Thursday. The change in policy comes six months after the controversial streamer was dropped by sponsors and business partners due to the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-sexting-twitch-ban-youtube-elden-ring-1851556854&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-sexting-twitch-ban-youtube-elden-ring-1851556854">circumstances surrounding a 2020 lifetime Twitch ban</a></span>.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/drdisrespect-twitch-ban-minor-youtube-monetization-1851752083&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/drdisrespect-twitch-ban-minor-youtube-monetization-1851752083">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3d9fa8e1aa85cd5bd63488cc3c3075d6" data-recommend-id="image://3d9fa8e1aa85cd5bd63488cc3c3075d6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1200" data-height="658" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Cover art shows Final Fantasy VI. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Cover art shows Final Fantasy VI. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Square Enix / Moby Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3d9fa8e1aa85cd5bd63488cc3c3075d6" data-recommend-id="image://3d9fa8e1aa85cd5bd63488cc3c3075d6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1200" data-height="658" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Cover art shows Final Fantasy VI. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Final Fantasy VI</em> is <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-vi-retrospective-simply-the-best-1792398695&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-vi-retrospective-simply-the-best-1792398695">one of the best games ever made</a></span>. Fans have been coasting off that high for decades, even as modern homages seek to recreate the magic of the original. The lead creative behind the beloved RPG series, Hironobu Sakaguchi, now says making a proper successor to the 1994 SNES classic will be his final mission. - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-6-sequel-hironobu-sakaguchi-fantasian-1851749344&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/final-fantasy-6-sequel-hironobu-sakaguchi-fantasian-1851749344">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="8c2e9604cc444f36594c0550e10fe910" data-recommend-id="image://8c2e9604cc444f36594c0550e10fe910" data-format="jpg" data-width="2000" data-height="1125" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A space ship encounters a big green planet. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A space ship encounters a big green planet. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Hello Games</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="8c2e9604cc444f36594c0550e10fe910" data-recommend-id="image://8c2e9604cc444f36594c0550e10fe910" data-format="jpg" data-width="2000" data-height="1125" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A space ship encounters a big green planet. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Now in its ninth year, the overwhelmingly expansive sci-fi survival sim<em> No Man’s Sky</em> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/no-man-sky-worlds-5-0-patch-art-graphics-ps5-sale-1851596991&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/no-man-sky-worlds-5-0-patch-art-graphics-ps5-sale-1851596991">is transforming yet again</a></span>. Another massive overhaul to the look and feel of its planets and solar systems has arrived in the form of the new Worlds Part II update<em>. </em>It’s the latest evolution of the game thanks to Hello Games’ ongoing work on its upcoming open-world survival RPG, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/no-mans-sky-light-no-fire-open-world-trailer-1851083189&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/no-mans-sky-light-no-fire-open-world-trailer-1851083189"><em>Light No Fire</em></a></span>.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/no-mans-sky-worlds-part-2-update-patch-light-no-fire-1851750164&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/no-mans-sky-worlds-part-2-update-patch-light-no-fire-1851750164">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3ade52118eeef6669e77b41524b386ec" data-recommend-id="image://3ade52118eeef6669e77b41524b386ec" data-format="png" data-width="2742" data-height="1541" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mass Effect Legacy Collection art shows the series' characters. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mass Effect Legacy Collection art shows the series' characters. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->BioWare / EA</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3ade52118eeef6669e77b41524b386ec" data-recommend-id="image://3ade52118eeef6669e77b41524b386ec" data-format="png" data-width="2742" data-height="1541" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mass Effect Legacy Collection art shows the series' characters. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>What’s left of BioWare, the renowned RPG powerhouse behind beloved franchises like <em>Dragon Age</em>, <em>Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic</em>, and the original <em>Baldur’s Gate</em> games? It’s a hard question to answer in 2025 after multiple rounds of layoffs and restructurings as the studio pivots between <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2024-11-01/-dragon-age-the-veilguard-faced-turbulent-development-high-stakes-at-bioware&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2024-11-01/-dragon-age-the-veilguard-faced-turbulent-development-high-stakes-at-bioware" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">the character-driven stories fans love</a></span> and the <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/how-biowares-anthem-went-wrong-1833731964?_gl=1*1wyggtm*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODE3Mzk3Ny4zNTAuMS4xNzM4MTc1NzgzLjM1LjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/how-biowares-anthem-went-wrong-1833731964?_gl=1*1wyggtm*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczODE3Mzk3Ny4zNTAuMS4xNzM4MTc1NzgzLjM1LjAuMA..">live-service gaming models investors want</a></span>. The only thing that seems certain is that the studio’s entire fate feels like it’s riding on <em>Mass Effect 5</em>, a game that’s still a long ways off.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mass-effect-5-bioware-dragon-age-veilguard-dlc-layoffs-1851750767&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mass-effect-5-bioware-dragon-age-veilguard-dlc-layoffs-1851750767">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="e3a46cdfde8a4e73cd725ea34344bf72" data-recommend-id="image://e3a46cdfde8a4e73cd725ea34344bf72" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Palkia is shown standing in the middle of Spear Pillar as pink spacial tears surround it." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Palkia is shown standing in the middle of Spear Pillar as pink spacial tears surround it." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Pokémon Company</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e3a46cdfde8a4e73cd725ea34344bf72" data-recommend-id="image://e3a46cdfde8a4e73cd725ea34344bf72" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Palkia is shown standing in the middle of Spear Pillar as pink spacial tears surround it." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Pokémon </em>card art is always fantastic, but my god, <em>Pokémon Trading Card Game Pocket</em>’s latest line of full-art cards is particularly exceptional. The “Space-Time Smackdown” set will be released on the app on January 30, primarily featuring Pokémon from the Nintendo DS games <em>Diamond </em>and <em>Pearl</em>. I am a Sinnoh sicko, so seeing Pokémon from that region like my boys Torterra, the grass/ground-type tortoise with a whole ecosystem on the back of its shell, and Palkia, the dragon god of space, featured in any capacity is alright by me. I’ve mostly stopped checking in on <em>TCGP</em>, but these exceptional full arts will get me back. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-trading-card-game-pocket-space-time-smackdown-1851750811&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/pokemon-trading-card-game-pocket-space-time-smackdown-1851750811">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
